# **Power Automate Actions - Complete List with Explanation & Examples**  

## **üîπ Core Actions (Built-in Actions)**  
These actions are available by default and are used for general logic and data manipulation.  

### **1Ô∏è‚É£ Control Actions (For Logic & Branching)**  
- **Condition** ‚Üí Used for If-Else logic.  
  - *Example:* If an employee‚Äôs leave balance is less than 5 days, send an approval request to HR; otherwise, approve automatically.  
- **Switch** ‚Üí Used when multiple conditions need to be checked.  
  - *Example:* If the request is for IT, send it to the IT team; if HR, send it to HR.  
- **Apply to Each** ‚Üí Loops through a collection (array).  
  - *Example:* For each row in an Excel file, create a new item in SharePoint.  
- **Do Until** ‚Üí Loops until a condition is met.  
  - *Example:* Keep checking an approval status until it is approved.  
- **Scope** ‚Üí Groups multiple actions together.  
  - *Example:* Combine all error-handling steps in a single scope.  

---

### **2Ô∏è‚É£ Variable Actions (For Storing & Manipulating Data)**  
- **Initialize Variable** ‚Üí Creates a variable to store data.  
  - *Example:* Store the current user‚Äôs email in a variable.  
- **Set Variable** ‚Üí Assigns a new value to a variable.  
  - *Example:* Set a variable ‚ÄúApprovalStatus‚Äù to ‚ÄúApproved.‚Äù  
- **Increment/Decrement Variable** ‚Üí Increases or decreases a variable‚Äôs value.  
  - *Example:* Increase a counter every time an email is sent.  
- **Append to String Variable** ‚Üí Adds text to a string variable.  
  - *Example:* Store a list of rejected employee requests in a single variable.  

---

### **3Ô∏è‚É£ Data Operations (For Handling JSON, Text, and Collections)**  
- **Compose** ‚Üí Stores a value temporarily for reuse.  
  - *Example:* Store a complex JSON structure in a compose action.  
- **Parse JSON** ‚Üí Extracts data from JSON format.  
  - *Example:* Parse API response data from a weather service.  
- **Select** ‚Üí Transforms array data.  
  - *Example:* Extract only email addresses from a list of users.  
- **Filter Array** ‚Üí Retrieves specific items from an array.  
  - *Example:* Get only pending leave requests from a dataset.  

---

### **4Ô∏è‚É£ Date & Time Actions (For Working with Time Values)**  
- **Convert Time Zone** ‚Üí Changes the time zone of a date/time value.  
  - *Example:* Convert UTC time to Indian Standard Time (IST).  
- **Add to Time** ‚Üí Adds time to a given date.  
  - *Example:* Add 30 days to today‚Äôs date for a task deadline.  
- **Subtract from Time** ‚Üí Subtracts time from a given date.  
  - *Example:* Subtract 7 days to find the last week's date.  

---

### **5Ô∏è‚É£ HTTP Actions (For Calling External APIs)**  
- **HTTP** ‚Üí Sends an API request.  
  - *Example:* Call a weather API to get live updates.  
- **HTTP with Azure AD** ‚Üí Calls APIs with authentication.  
  - *Example:* Retrieve user details from Azure AD securely.  

---

## **üîπ Microsoft 365 Actions**  

### **6Ô∏è‚É£ SharePoint Actions (For Working with SharePoint Data)**  
- **Get Items** ‚Üí Retrieves items from a SharePoint list.  
  - *Example:* Fetch all open support tickets from a SharePoint list.  
- **Create Item** ‚Üí Adds a new item to a SharePoint list.  
  - *Example:* Create a new entry when a form is submitted.  
- **Update Item** ‚Üí Modifies an existing SharePoint list item.  
  - *Example:* Update an approval request‚Äôs status to ‚ÄúApproved.‚Äù  
- **Delete Item** ‚Üí Removes an item from a SharePoint list.  
  - *Example:* Remove a completed task from the list.  

---

### **7Ô∏è‚É£ Outlook & Email Actions (For Automating Emails)**  
- **Send an Email** ‚Üí Sends an email using Outlook or Gmail.  
  - *Example:* Send approval status updates to employees.  
- **Get Emails** ‚Üí Retrieves emails from an inbox.  
  - *Example:* Fetch unread emails for processing in Power Automate.  
- **Delete Email** ‚Üí Deletes an email from an inbox.  
  - *Example:* Automatically delete spam emails from a folder.  

---

### **8Ô∏è‚É£ Power Apps Actions (For Integrating with Power Apps)**  
- **PowerApps (V2)** ‚Üí Triggers a flow from Power Apps.  
  - *Example:* Start an approval process when a user submits a form in Power Apps.  
- **Respond to PowerApps** ‚Üí Sends a response back to Power Apps.  
  - *Example:* Send approval status back to Power Apps.  

---

### **9Ô∏è‚É£ Microsoft Teams Actions (For Automation in Teams)**  
- **Post a Message** ‚Üí Sends a message in a Teams channel.  
  - *Example:* Notify a team when a document is uploaded.  
- **Create a Team** ‚Üí Creates a new Microsoft Teams group.  
  - *Example:* Automatically create a team when a new project starts.  
- **Add Member to Team** ‚Üí Adds a user to a team.  
  - *Example:* Add a new employee to the IT support team.  

---

### **üîü Dataverse Actions (For Working with Microsoft Dataverse)**  
- **List Rows** ‚Üí Retrieves rows from a Dataverse table.  
  - *Example:* Fetch all customer orders.  
- **Add a Row** ‚Üí Inserts a new row.  
  - *Example:* Add a new lead into Dataverse CRM.  
- **Update a Row** ‚Üí Modifies an existing row.  
  - *Example:* Change a lead‚Äôs status from ‚ÄúNew‚Äù to ‚ÄúQualified.‚Äù  

---

## **üîπ External & Third-Party Integrations**  

### **1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ SQL Server Actions (For Working with SQL Databases)**  
- **Execute a SQL Query** ‚Üí Runs a query against a SQL database.  
  - *Example:* Get all pending invoices from a database.  
- **Insert Row** ‚Üí Adds a record to a SQL table.  
  - *Example:* Add a new employee record.  
- **Update Row** ‚Üí Modifies a record in a SQL table.  
  - *Example:* Update salary information for an employee.  

---

### **1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ OneDrive Actions (For Working with Cloud Storage)**  
- **Create File** ‚Üí Creates a file in OneDrive.  
  - *Example:* Save an email attachment to OneDrive automatically.  
- **Delete File** ‚Üí Removes a file from OneDrive.  
  - *Example:* Delete old backup files automatically.  
- **Get File Content** ‚Üí Retrieves file content.  
  - *Example:* Extract text from a PDF file.  

---

### **1Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ Social Media Actions (For Posting & Retrieving Data)**  
- **Post a Tweet** ‚Üí Sends a tweet from an account.  
  - *Example:* Auto-post company updates on Twitter.  
- **Create a LinkedIn Post** ‚Üí Creates a post on LinkedIn.  
  - *Example:* Publish job openings on LinkedIn.  

---

### **1Ô∏è‚É£4Ô∏è‚É£ AI Builder Actions (For AI-Powered Automation)**  
- **Extract Text from Image** ‚Üí Uses OCR to extract text.  
  - *Example:* Read invoices and store data in SharePoint.  
- **Analyze Sentiment** ‚Üí Detects sentiment in text.  
  - *Example:* Analyze customer feedback and flag negative comments.  

---

## **üìå Summary**  
Power Automate provides **hundreds of actions** across **built-in controls, Microsoft 365, Dataverse, external services, and AI Builder**.  

